    {
      "id": 18,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [40, 940],
      "size": [780, 720],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 0,
      "mode": 0,
      "properties": {"text": ""},
      "widgets_values": [
        "🔬 HIDDEN GEOMETRY TECH DEMO — X-ray behind the cathedral columns + DOLLY-IN\nEXPERIMENTAL / RESEARCH-ONLY (upstream LaRI repo has NO license)\n\nSETUP (once): clone LaRI + point at it —\n    git clone https://github.com/ruili3/lari.git\nBlank lari_path uses the ATLAS_LARI_PATH env var if set; else paste the clone\npath into the 🔬 node. Weights (~1.3GB) download from HuggingFace on first\nrun. Needs CUDA; no PyTorch3D. See INSTALL.md 'Hidden-Geometry Prediction'.\n\nARCHITECTURE (calibrated 2026-07-09 — measured, not guessed):\n1. ONE solve + ONE shared DA3 depth (solved focal).\n2. BASE GEOMETRY: AtlasDeriveReliefMesh on the ORIGINAL depth — a full-depth\n   relief mesh PLUS its projection_backdrop catch-all plane. This is what\n   guarantees no black tearing at/near the recovered camera view. (An\n   earlier fg/bg-banded version of this graph had NO base mesh — the deep\n   colonnade shredded into 20-35% black. Banding suits scenes with separated\n   depth clusters; a cathedral is one CONTINUOUS recession.)\n3. SolidMask 0 → exclude_mask on BOTH geometry nodes: this is an interior —\n   an explicit empty mask REPLACES the internal sky heuristic, which\n   otherwise eats the vault ('above horizon + far' = classic false sky).\n4. X-RAY: AtlasDepthLayerMask in MANUAL mode, far_pct 0.30 = only the\n   NEAREST columns feed the 🔬 node's restrict_mask (restricting to the\n   whole near half made LaRI push visible walls/floor deep — measured\n   worse). clear_rel 0.30 = conservative surface acceptance.\n5. The bg_xray band (background side of the 0.55 split) builds its mesh\n   from the PATCHED depth: real predicted geometry sits BEHIND the columns,\n   layered behind the base mesh, waiting to be revealed.\n\nSLIDER NOTE (answers 'what should near/far be?'): when a band_split wire is\nconnected AND band_side is foreground/background, the near/far sliders are\nIGNORED — the split node is the single authority. Sliders only matter in\nband_side=manual (that's exactly how the restrict-mask node above uses\nfar_pct 0.30).\n\n🎥 THE DOLLY-IN DEMO\n1. Queue once (viewport shows the projected nave; report shows registration).\n2. In the viewport: 🎥 Camera Path → 'Dolly In' preset → Apply Preset →\n   ▶ Play to preview. The dolly drives the RENDER camera between the\n   columns; the projection stays anchored to the recovered camera, so\n   disocclusions open at the column silhouettes — and land on the X-ray\n   band's PREDICTED geometry instead of black.\n3. ⏺ Bake Proxy Path — re-queues automatically; the baked frames flow into\n   VideoCombine Plus → atlas_cathedral_dolly.mp4 in ComfyUI's output folder.\n4. For the DCC handoff, UNMUTE the AtlasExportCameraPathUSD node (muted by\n   default because it errors — deliberately — when no path is baked yet)\n   and re-queue: camera_path.usda alongside.\n\nA/B: mute the 🔬 node (Ctrl+M) and rewire the bg_xray band's depth to the\nAtlasDepthMap to compare diffusion-only reveals on the same dolly."
      ]
    }
